cmd/config/get_context.go.message:
This bug could be fixed much simpler. First of all, I do believe that this output should be YAML compatible, so we have to avoid to print additional labels like "Current context: " and so on. Secondly, to print all the contexts all you have to do is to get Contexts map from Config (it contains all required information) and serialize it using yaml.Marshal(). No other changes needed, it can look like this:

                        if o.Name == "" && !o.CurrentContext {
				contexts := airconfig.Contexts
				if len(contexts) == 0 {
					fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), "No Contexts found in the configuration.")
				}
				data, err := yaml.Marshal(contexts)
				if err != nil {
					return err
				}
				fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), string(data))
				return nil
			}

It is better to add a method to the config package

func (c *Config) StringifyContexts() string {
	data, err := yaml.Marshal(&c.Contexts)
	if err != nil {
		return ""
	}
	return string(data) + fmt.Sprintf("\ncurrentContext: %s", c.CurrentContext)
}
and then here you can just use something like 

if len(airconfig.GetContexts()) == 0 {
	fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), "No Contexts found in the configuration.")
}
fmt.Fprintln(cmd.OutOrStdout(), airconfig.StringifyContexts())

